[[Image:Victor JustForLaughs trademark.jpg|thumb|right|120px|Just Victor.]] [[Image:Justforlaughs2.JPG|thumb|right|150px|Inflatable Victor with his wife, Rose]]
'''Victor''' is the [[mascot]] and [[logo]] for the [[comedy festival]] [[Just for Laughs]]. It was designed by [[Vittorio Fiorucci]] of the Canadian Design Resource company.
The image was inspired by a [[monster]] that preys on Montreal.<ref>{{cite web|author=Todd Falkowsky |url=http://www.canadiandesignresource.ca/officialgallery/logo/victor-just-for-laughs-logomascot/ |title=The CANADIAN DESIGN RESOURCE » "Victor" Just For Laughs Logo/Mascot |publisher=Canadiandesignresource.ca |date=2009-08-10 |accessdate=2010-07-30}}</ref> The logo can be seen across the world on posters, T-shirts, event site markers, costumes, and inflatables.
In 2005 the character was redesigned by animator [[Alan Best (filmmaker)|Alan Best]] at the behest of advertising agency [[Cossette, Inc.|Cossette]] as part of a comprehensive graphic overhaul of the Just For Laughs brand. In 2007, "Rose" was created, a character to be the wife of Victor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbizz.net/articles/20080625113319/grand_charivarir_juste_pour_rire_retour_rose_entrevue.html |title=Le Grand Charivarir de Juste pour rire: le retour de Rose (entrevue) - Showbizz québécois |publisher=Showbizz.net |date=2008-06-25 |accessdate=2010-07-30}}</ref>
